{{see|deja-vu|déjà-vu}}

==English==

===Etymology===
French ''[[déjà]]'', "already", + ''[[vu]]'', "seen", past participle of ''[[voir]]'', "to see"

===Pronunciation===
dé·jà vu
*IPA:/ˌdeɪʒɑː ˈvuː
*SAMPA: /<tt>%deIZA: "vu:</tt>/
*AHD: dā"zhä vo͞o'
DEI-zha voo

===Noun===
'''déjà vu'''

# Something which one has or suspects to have [[see]]n or [[experience]]d before, especially when that's not the case.
EX: ''Have I done this before?  Talk about [[deja vu]]''.

===Alternative spellings===
*[[deja vu]]

